2691void CGOpenMPRuntimeNVPTX::emitCriticalRegion(
2692 CodeGenFunction &CGF, StringRef CriticalName,
2693 const RegionCodeGenTy &CriticalOpGen, SourceLocation Loc,
2694 const Expr *Hint) {
2695 llvm::BasicBlock *LoopBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("omp.critical.loop");
2696 llvm::BasicBlock *TestBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("omp.critical.test");
2697 llvm::BasicBlock *SyncBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("omp.critical.sync");
2698 llvm::BasicBlock *BodyBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("omp.critical.body");
2699 llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("omp.critical.exit");
2700
2701 // Fetch team-local id of the thread.
2702 llvm::Value *ThreadID = getNVPTXThreadID(CGF);
2703
2704 // Get the width of the team.
2705 llvm::Value *TeamWidth = getNVPTXNumThreads(CGF);
2706
2707 // Initialize the counter variable for the loop.
2708 QualType Int32Ty =
2709 CGF.getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(/*DestWidth=*/32, /*Signed=*/0);
2710 Address Counter = CGF.CreateMemTemp(Int32Ty, "critical_counter");
2711 LValue CounterLVal = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Counter, Int32Ty);
2712 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int32Ty), CounterLVal,
2713 /*isInit=*/true);
2714
2715 // Block checks if loop counter exceeds upper bound.
2716 CGF.EmitBlock(LoopBB);
2717 llvm::Value *CounterVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CounterLVal, Loc);
2718 llvm::Value *CmpLoopBound = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpSLT(CounterVal, TeamWidth);
2719 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(CmpLoopBound, TestBB, ExitBB);
2720
2721 // Block tests which single thread should execute region, and which threads
2722 // should go straight to synchronisation point.
2723 CGF.EmitBlock(TestBB);
2724 CounterVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CounterLVal, Loc);
2725 llvm::Value *CmpThreadToCounter =
2726 CGF.Builder.CreateICmpEQ(ThreadID, CounterVal);
2727 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(CmpThreadToCounter, BodyBB, SyncBB);
2728
2729 // Block emits the body of the critical region.
2730 CGF.EmitBlock(BodyBB);
2731
2732 // Output the critical statement.
2733 CGOpenMPRuntime::emitCriticalRegion(CGF, CriticalName, CriticalOpGen, Loc,
2734 Hint);
2735
2736 // After the body surrounded by the critical region, the single executing
2737 // thread will jump to the synchronisation point.
2738 // Block waits for all threads in current team to finish then increments the
2739 // counter variable and returns to the loop.
2740 CGF.EmitBlock(SyncBB);
2741 emitBarrierCall(CGF, Loc, OMPD_unknown, /*EmitChecks=*/false,
2742 /*ForceSimpleCall=*/true);
2743
2744 llvm::Value *IncCounterVal =
2745 CGF.Builder.CreateNSWAdd(CounterVal, CGF.Builder.getInt32(1));
2746 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(IncCounterVal, CounterLVal);
2747 CGF.EmitBranch(LoopBB);
2748
2749 // Block that is reached when all threads in the team complete the region.
2750 CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
2751}

2753/// Cast value to the specified type.
2754static llvm::Value *castValueToType(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *Val,
2755 QualType ValTy, QualType CastTy,
2756 SourceLocation Loc) {
2757 assert(!CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(CastTy).isZero() &&
2758 "Cast type must sized.");
2759 assert(!CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ValTy).isZero() &&
2760 "Val type must sized.");
2761 llvm::Type *LLVMCastTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(CastTy);
2762 if (ValTy == CastTy)
2763 return Val;
2764 if (CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ValTy) ==
2765 CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(CastTy))
2766 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Val, LLVMCastTy);
2767 if (CastTy->isIntegerType() && ValTy->isIntegerType())
2768 return CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(Val, LLVMCastTy,
2769 CastTy->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation());
2770 Address CastItem = CGF.CreateMemTemp(CastTy);
2771 Address ValCastItem = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
2772 CastItem, Val->getType()->getPointerTo(CastItem.getAddressSpace()));
2773 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Val, ValCastItem, /*Volatile=*/false, ValTy);
2774 return CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CastItem, /*Volatile=*/false, CastTy, Loc);
2775}

2777/// This function creates calls to one of two shuffle functions to copy
2778/// variables between lanes in a warp.
2779static llvm::Value *createRuntimeShuffleFunction(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2780 llvm::Value *Elem,
2781 QualType ElemType,
2782 llvm::Value *Offset,
2783 SourceLocation Loc) {
2784 CodeGenModule &CGM = CGF.CGM;
2785 CGBuilderTy &Bld = CGF.Builder;
2786 CGOpenMPRuntimeNVPTX &RT =
2787 *(static_cast<CGOpenMPRuntimeNVPTX *>(&CGM.getOpenMPRuntime()));
2788
2789 CharUnits Size = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ElemType);
2790 assert(Size.getQuantity() <= 8 &&
2791 "Unsupported bitwidth in shuffle instruction.");
2792
2793 OpenMPRTLFunctionNVPTX ShuffleFn = Size.getQuantity() <= 4
2794 ? OMPRTL_NVPTX__kmpc_shuffle_int32
2795 : OMPRTL_NVPTX__kmpc_shuffle_int64;
2796
2797 // Cast all types to 32- or 64-bit values before calling shuffle routines.
2798 QualType CastTy = CGF.getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(
2799 Size.getQuantity() <= 4 ? 32 : 64, /*Signed=*/1);
2800 llvm::Value *ElemCast = castValueToType(CGF, Elem, ElemType, CastTy, Loc);
2801 llvm::Value *WarpSize =
2802 Bld.CreateIntCast(getNVPTXWarpSize(CGF), CGM.Int16Ty, /*isSigned=*/true);
2803
2804 llvm::Value *ShuffledVal = CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
2805 RT.createNVPTXRuntimeFunction(ShuffleFn), {ElemCast, Offset, WarpSize});
2806
2807 return castValueToType(CGF, ShuffledVal, CastTy, ElemType, Loc);
2808}

2810static void shuffleAndStore(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address SrcAddr,
2811 Address DestAddr, QualType ElemType,
2812 llvm::Value *Offset, SourceLocation Loc) {
2813 CGBuilderTy &Bld = CGF.Builder;
2814
2815 CharUnits Size = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ElemType);
2816 // Create the loop over the big sized data.
2817 // ptr = (void*)Elem;
2818 // ptrEnd = (void*) Elem + 1;
2819 // Step = 8;
2820 // while (ptr + Step < ptrEnd)
2821 // shuffle((int64_t)*ptr);
2822 // Step = 4;
2823 // while (ptr + Step < ptrEnd)
2824 // shuffle((int32_t)*ptr);
2825 // ...
2826 Address ElemPtr = DestAddr;
2827 Address Ptr = SrcAddr;
2828 Address PtrEnd = Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
2829 Bld.CreateConstGEP(SrcAddr, 1), CGF.VoidPtrTy);
2830 for (int IntSize = 8; IntSize >= 1; IntSize /= 2) {
2831 if (Size < CharUnits::fromQuantity(IntSize))
2832 continue;
2833 QualType IntType = CGF.getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(
2834 CGF.getContext().toBits(CharUnits::fromQuantity(IntSize)),
2835 /*Signed=*/1);
2836 llvm::Type *IntTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(IntType);
2837 Ptr = Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Ptr, IntTy->getPointerTo());
2838 ElemPtr =
2839 Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(ElemPtr, IntTy->getPointerTo());
2840 if (Size.getQuantity() / IntSize > 1) {
2841 llvm::BasicBlock *PreCondBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".shuffle.pre_cond");
2842 llvm::BasicBlock *ThenBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".shuffle.then");
2843 llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".shuffle.exit");
2844 llvm::BasicBlock *CurrentBB = Bld.GetInsertBlock();
2845 CGF.EmitBlock(PreCondBB);
2846 llvm::PHINode *PhiSrc =
2847 Bld.CreatePHI(Ptr.getType(), /*NumReservedValues=*/2);
2848 PhiSrc->addIncoming(Ptr.getPointer(), CurrentBB);
2849 llvm::PHINode *PhiDest =
2850 Bld.CreatePHI(ElemPtr.getType(), /*NumReservedValues=*/2);
2851 PhiDest->addIncoming(ElemPtr.getPointer(), CurrentBB);
2852 Ptr = Address(PhiSrc, Ptr.getAlignment());
2853 ElemPtr = Address(PhiDest, ElemPtr.getAlignment());
2854 llvm::Value *PtrDiff = Bld.CreatePtrDiff(
2855 PtrEnd.getPointer(), Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
2856 Ptr.getPointer(), CGF.VoidPtrTy));
2857 Bld.CreateCondBr(Bld.CreateICmpSGT(PtrDiff, Bld.getInt64(IntSize - 1)),
2858 ThenBB, ExitBB);
2859 CGF.EmitBlock(ThenBB);
2860 llvm::Value *Res = createRuntimeShuffleFunction(
2861 CGF, CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(Ptr, /*Volatile=*/false, IntType, Loc),
2862 IntType, Offset, Loc);
2863 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Res, ElemPtr, /*Volatile=*/false, IntType);
2864 Address LocalPtr = Bld.CreateConstGEP(Ptr, 1);
2865 Address LocalElemPtr = Bld.CreateConstGEP(ElemPtr, 1);
2866 PhiSrc->addIncoming(LocalPtr.getPointer(), ThenBB);
2867 PhiDest->addIncoming(LocalElemPtr.getPointer(), ThenBB);
2868 CGF.EmitBranch(PreCondBB);
2869 CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB);
2870 } else {
2871 llvm::Value *Res = createRuntimeShuffleFunction(
2872 CGF, CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(Ptr, /*Volatile=*/false, IntType, Loc),
2873 IntType, Offset, Loc);
2874 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Res, ElemPtr, /*Volatile=*/false, IntType);
2875 Ptr = Bld.CreateConstGEP(Ptr, 1);
2876 ElemPtr = Bld.CreateConstGEP(ElemPtr, 1);
2877 }
2878 Size = Size % IntSize;
2879 }
2880}

2882namespace {
2883enum CopyAction : unsigned {
2884 // RemoteLaneToThread: Copy over a Reduce list from a remote lane in
2885 // the warp using shuffle instructions.
2886 RemoteLaneToThread,
2887 // ThreadCopy: Make a copy of a Reduce list on the thread's stack.
2888 ThreadCopy,
2889 // ThreadToScratchpad: Copy a team-reduced array to the scratchpad.
2890 ThreadToScratchpad,
2891 // ScratchpadToThread: Copy from a scratchpad array in global memory
2892 // containing team-reduced data to a thread's stack.
2893 ScratchpadToThread,
2894};
2895} // namespace
2896
2897struct CopyOptionsTy {
2898 llvm::Value *RemoteLaneOffset;
2899 llvm::Value *ScratchpadIndex;
2900 llvm::Value *ScratchpadWidth;
2901};
2902
2903/// Emit instructions to copy a Reduce list, which contains partially
2904/// aggregated values, in the specified direction.
2905static void emitReductionListCopy(
2906 CopyAction Action, CodeGenFunction &CGF, QualType ReductionArrayTy,
2907 ArrayRef<const Expr *> Privates, Address SrcBase, Address DestBase,
2908 CopyOptionsTy CopyOptions = {nullptr, nullptr, nullptr}) {
2909
2910 CodeGenModule &CGM = CGF.CGM;
2911 ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
2912 CGBuilderTy &Bld = CGF.Builder;
2913
2914 llvm::Value *RemoteLaneOffset = CopyOptions.RemoteLaneOffset;
2915 llvm::Value *ScratchpadIndex = CopyOptions.ScratchpadIndex;
2916 llvm::Value *ScratchpadWidth = CopyOptions.ScratchpadWidth;
2917
2918 // Iterates, element-by-element, through the source Reduce list and
2919 // make a copy.
2920 unsigned Idx = 0;
2921 unsigned Size = Privates.size();
2922 for (const Expr *Private : Privates) {
2923 Address SrcElementAddr = Address::invalid();
2924 Address DestElementAddr = Address::invalid();
2925 Address DestElementPtrAddr = Address::invalid();
2926 // Should we shuffle in an element from a remote lane?
2927 bool ShuffleInElement = false;
2928 // Set to true to update the pointer in the dest Reduce list to a
2929 // newly created element.
2930 bool UpdateDestListPtr = false;
2931 // Increment the src or dest pointer to the scratchpad, for each
2932 // new element.
2933 bool IncrScratchpadSrc = false;
2934 bool IncrScratchpadDest = false;
2935
2936 switch (Action) {
2937 case RemoteLaneToThread: {
2938 // Step 1.1: Get the address for the src element in the Reduce list.
2939 Address SrcElementPtrAddr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(SrcBase, Idx);
2940 SrcElementAddr = CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(
2941 SrcElementPtrAddr,
2942 C.getPointerType(Private->getType())->castAs<PointerType>());
2943
2944 // Step 1.2: Create a temporary to store the element in the destination
2945 // Reduce list.
2946 DestElementPtrAddr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(DestBase, Idx);
2947 DestElementAddr =
2948 CGF.CreateMemTemp(Private->getType(), ".omp.reduction.element");
2949 ShuffleInElement = true;
2950 UpdateDestListPtr = true;
2951 break;
2952 }
2953 case ThreadCopy: {
2954 // Step 1.1: Get the address for the src element in the Reduce list.
2955 Address SrcElementPtrAddr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(SrcBase, Idx);
2956 SrcElementAddr = CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(
2957 SrcElementPtrAddr,
2958 C.getPointerType(Private->getType())->castAs<PointerType>());
2959
2960 // Step 1.2: Get the address for dest element. The destination
2961 // element has already been created on the thread's stack.
2962 DestElementPtrAddr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(DestBase, Idx);
2963 DestElementAddr = CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(
2964 DestElementPtrAddr,
2965 C.getPointerType(Private->getType())->castAs<PointerType>());
2966 break;
2967 }
2968 case ThreadToScratchpad: {
2969 // Step 1.1: Get the address for the src element in the Reduce list.
2970 Address SrcElementPtrAddr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(SrcBase, Idx);
2971 SrcElementAddr = CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(
2972 SrcElementPtrAddr,
2973 C.getPointerType(Private->getType())->castAs<PointerType>());
2974
2975 // Step 1.2: Get the address for dest element:
2976 // address = base + index * ElementSizeInChars.
2977 llvm::Value *ElementSizeInChars = CGF.getTypeSize(Private->getType());
2978 llvm::Value *CurrentOffset =
2979 Bld.CreateNUWMul(ElementSizeInChars, ScratchpadIndex);
2980 llvm::Value *ScratchPadElemAbsolutePtrVal =
2981 Bld.CreateNUWAdd(DestBase.getPointer(), CurrentOffset);
2982 ScratchPadElemAbsolutePtrVal =
2983 Bld.CreateIntToPtr(ScratchPadElemAbsolutePtrVal, CGF.VoidPtrTy);
2984 DestElementAddr = Address(ScratchPadElemAbsolutePtrVal,
2985 C.getTypeAlignInChars(Private->getType()));
2986 IncrScratchpadDest = true;
2987 break;
2988 }
2989 case ScratchpadToThread: {
2990 // Step 1.1: Get the address for the src element in the scratchpad.
2991 // address = base + index * ElementSizeInChars.
2992 llvm::Value *ElementSizeInChars = CGF.getTypeSize(Private->getType());
2993 llvm::Value *CurrentOffset =
2994 Bld.CreateNUWMul(ElementSizeInChars, ScratchpadIndex);
2995 llvm::Value *ScratchPadElemAbsolutePtrVal =
2996 Bld.CreateNUWAdd(SrcBase.getPointer(), CurrentOffset);
2997 ScratchPadElemAbsolutePtrVal =
2998 Bld.CreateIntToPtr(ScratchPadElemAbsolutePtrVal, CGF.VoidPtrTy);
2999 SrcElementAddr = Address(ScratchPadElemAbsolutePtrVal,
3000 C.getTypeAlignInChars(Private->getType()));
3001 IncrScratchpadSrc = true;
3002
3003 // Step 1.2: Create a temporary to store the element in the destination
3004 // Reduce list.
3005 DestElementPtrAddr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(DestBase, Idx);
3006 DestElementAddr =
3007 CGF.CreateMemTemp(Private->getType(), ".omp.reduction.element");
3008 UpdateDestListPtr = true;
3009 break;
3010 }
3011 }
3012
3013 // Regardless of src and dest of copy, we emit the load of src
3014 // element as this is required in all directions
3015 SrcElementAddr = Bld.CreateElementBitCast(
3016 SrcElementAddr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Private->getType()));
3017 DestElementAddr = Bld.CreateElementBitCast(DestElementAddr,
3018 SrcElementAddr.getElementType());
3019
3020 // Now that all active lanes have read the element in the
3021 // Reduce list, shuffle over the value from the remote lane.
3022 if (ShuffleInElement) {
3023 shuffleAndStore(CGF, SrcElementAddr, DestElementAddr, Private->getType(),
3024 RemoteLaneOffset, Private->getExprLoc());
3025 } else {
3026 switch (CGF.getEvaluationKind(Private->getType())) {
3027 case TEK_Scalar: {
3028 llvm::Value *Elem =
3029 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(SrcElementAddr, /*Volatile=*/false,
3030 Private->getType(), Private->getExprLoc());
3031 // Store the source element value to the dest element address.
3032 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Elem, DestElementAddr, /*Volatile=*/false,
3033 Private->getType());
3034 break;
3035 }
3036 case TEK_Complex: {
3037 CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy Elem = CGF.EmitLoadOfComplex(
3038 CGF.MakeAddrLValue(SrcElementAddr, Private->getType()),
3039 Private->getExprLoc());
3040 CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(
3041 Elem, CGF.MakeAddrLValue(DestElementAddr, Private->getType()),
3042 /*isInit=*/false);
3043 break;
3044 }
3045 case TEK_Aggregate:
3046 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(
3047 CGF.MakeAddrLValue(DestElementAddr, Private->getType()),
3048 CGF.MakeAddrLValue(SrcElementAddr, Private->getType()),
3049 Private->getType(), AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap);
3050 break;
3051 }
3052 }
3053
3054 // Step 3.1: Modify reference in dest Reduce list as needed.
3055 // Modifying the reference in Reduce list to point to the newly
3056 // created element. The element is live in the current function
3057 // scope and that of functions it invokes (i.e., reduce_function).
3058 // RemoteReduceData[i] = (void*)&RemoteElem
3059 if (UpdateDestListPtr) {
3060 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3061 DestElementAddr.getPointer(), CGF.VoidPtrTy),
3062 DestElementPtrAddr, /*Volatile=*/false,
3063 C.VoidPtrTy);
3064 }
3065
3066 // Step 4.1: Increment SrcBase/DestBase so that it points to the starting
3067 // address of the next element in scratchpad memory, unless we're currently
3068 // processing the last one. Memory alignment is also taken care of here.
3069 if ((IncrScratchpadDest || IncrScratchpadSrc) && (Idx + 1 < Size)) {
3070 llvm::Value *ScratchpadBasePtr =
3071 IncrScratchpadDest ? DestBase.getPointer() : SrcBase.getPointer();
3072 llvm::Value *ElementSizeInChars = CGF.getTypeSize(Private->getType());
3073 ScratchpadBasePtr = Bld.CreateNUWAdd(
3074 ScratchpadBasePtr,
3075 Bld.CreateNUWMul(ScratchpadWidth, ElementSizeInChars));
3076
3077 // Take care of global memory alignment for performance
3078 ScratchpadBasePtr = Bld.CreateNUWSub(
3079 ScratchpadBasePtr, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.SizeTy, 1));
3080 ScratchpadBasePtr = Bld.CreateUDiv(
3081 ScratchpadBasePtr,
3082 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.SizeTy, GlobalMemoryAlignment));
3083 ScratchpadBasePtr = Bld.CreateNUWAdd(
3084 ScratchpadBasePtr, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.SizeTy, 1));
3085 ScratchpadBasePtr = Bld.CreateNUWMul(
3086 ScratchpadBasePtr,
3087 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.SizeTy, GlobalMemoryAlignment));
3088
3089 if (IncrScratchpadDest)
3090 DestBase = Address(ScratchpadBasePtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
3091 else /* IncrScratchpadSrc = true */
3092 SrcBase = Address(ScratchpadBasePtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
3093 }
3094
3095 ++Idx;
3096 }
3097}

3099/// This function emits a helper that gathers Reduce lists from the first
3100/// lane of every active warp to lanes in the first warp.
3101///
3102/// void inter_warp_copy_func(void* reduce_data, num_warps)
3103/// shared smem[warp_size];
3104/// For all data entries D in reduce_data:
3105/// sync
3106/// If (I am the first lane in each warp)
3107/// Copy my local D to smem[warp_id]
3108/// sync
3109/// if (I am the first warp)
3110/// Copy smem[thread_id] to my local D
3111static llvm::Value *emitInterWarpCopyFunction(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3112 ArrayRef<const Expr *> Privates,
3113 QualType ReductionArrayTy,
3114 SourceLocation Loc) {
3115 ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
3116 llvm::Module &M = CGM.getModule();
3117
3118 // ReduceList: thread local Reduce list.
3119 // At the stage of the computation when this function is called, partially
3120 // aggregated values reside in the first lane of every active warp.
3121 ImplicitParamDecl ReduceListArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3122 C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3123 // NumWarps: number of warps active in the parallel region. This could
3124 // be smaller than 32 (max warps in a CTA) for partial block reduction.
3125 ImplicitParamDecl NumWarpsArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3126 C.getIntTypeForBitwidth(32, /* Signed */ true),
3127 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3128 FunctionArgList Args;
3129 Args.push_back(&ReduceListArg);
3130 Args.push_back(&NumWarpsArg);
3131
3132 const CGFunctionInfo &CGFI =
3133 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(C.VoidTy, Args);
3134 auto *Fn = llvm::Function::Create(CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(CGFI),
3135 llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
3136 "_omp_reduction_inter_warp_copy_func", &M);
3137 CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, CGFI);
3138 Fn->setDoesNotRecurse();
3139 CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
3140 CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), C.VoidTy, Fn, CGFI, Args, Loc, Loc);
3141
3142 CGBuilderTy &Bld = CGF.Builder;
3143
3144 // This array is used as a medium to transfer, one reduce element at a time,
3145 // the data from the first lane of every warp to lanes in the first warp
3146 // in order to perform the final step of a reduction in a parallel region
3147 // (reduction across warps). The array is placed in NVPTX __shared__ memory
3148 // for reduced latency, as well as to have a distinct copy for concurrently
3149 // executing target regions. The array is declared with common linkage so
3150 // as to be shared across compilation units.
3151 StringRef TransferMediumName =
3152 "__openmp_nvptx_data_transfer_temporary_storage";
3153 llvm::GlobalVariable *TransferMedium =
3154 M.getGlobalVariable(TransferMediumName);
3155 if (!TransferMedium) {
3156 auto *Ty = llvm::ArrayType::get(CGM.Int32Ty, WarpSize);
3157 unsigned SharedAddressSpace = CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::cuda_shared);
3158 TransferMedium = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3159 M, Ty, /*isConstant=*/false, llvm::GlobalVariable::CommonLinkage,
3160 llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Ty), TransferMediumName,
3161 /*InsertBefore=*/nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
3162 SharedAddressSpace);
3163 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(TransferMedium);
3164 }
3165
3166 // Get the CUDA thread id of the current OpenMP thread on the GPU.
3167 llvm::Value *ThreadID = getNVPTXThreadID(CGF);
3168 // nvptx_lane_id = nvptx_id % warpsize
3169 llvm::Value *LaneID = getNVPTXLaneID(CGF);
3170 // nvptx_warp_id = nvptx_id / warpsize
3171 llvm::Value *WarpID = getNVPTXWarpID(CGF);
3172
3173 Address AddrReduceListArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ReduceListArg);
3174 unsigned DefaultAS = CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
3175 Address LocalReduceList(
3176 Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3177 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(AddrReduceListArg, /*Volatile=*/false,
3178 C.VoidPtrTy, Loc),
3179 CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ReductionArrayTy)->getPointerTo(DefaultAS)),
3180 CGF.getPointerAlign());
3181
3182 unsigned Idx = 0;
3183 for (const Expr *Private : Privates) {
3184 //
3185 // Warp master copies reduce element to transfer medium in __shared__
3186 // memory.
3187 //
3188 unsigned RealTySize =
3189 C.getTypeSizeInChars(Private->getType())
3190 .alignTo(C.getTypeAlignInChars(Private->getType()))
3191 .getQuantity();
3192 for (unsigned TySize = 4; TySize > 0 && RealTySize > 0; TySize /=2) {
3193 unsigned NumIters = RealTySize / TySize;
3194 if (NumIters == 0)
3195 continue;
3196 QualType CType = C.getIntTypeForBitwidth(
3197 C.toBits(CharUnits::fromQuantity(TySize)), /*Signed=*/1);
3198 llvm::Type *CopyType = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(CType);
3199 CharUnits Align = CharUnits::fromQuantity(TySize);
3200 llvm::Value *Cnt = nullptr;
3201 Address CntAddr = Address::invalid();
3202 llvm::BasicBlock *PrecondBB = nullptr;
3203 llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = nullptr;
3204 if (NumIters > 1) {
3205 CntAddr = CGF.CreateMemTemp(C.IntTy, ".cnt.addr");
3206 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.IntTy), CntAddr,
3207 /*Volatile=*/false, C.IntTy);
3208 PrecondBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("precond");
3209 ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("exit");
3210 llvm::BasicBlock *BodyBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("body");
3211 // There is no need to emit line number for unconditional branch.
3212 (void)ApplyDebugLocation::CreateEmpty(CGF);
3213 CGF.EmitBlock(PrecondBB);
3214 Cnt = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CntAddr, /*Volatile=*/false, C.IntTy, Loc);
3215 llvm::Value *Cmp =
3216 Bld.CreateICmpULT(Cnt, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, NumIters));
3217 Bld.CreateCondBr(Cmp, BodyBB, ExitBB);
3218 CGF.EmitBlock(BodyBB);
3219 }
3220 // kmpc_barrier.
3221 CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().emitBarrierCall(CGF, Loc, OMPD_unknown,
3222 /*EmitChecks=*/false,
3223 /*ForceSimpleCall=*/true);
3224 llvm::BasicBlock *ThenBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("then");
3225 llvm::BasicBlock *ElseBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("else");
3226 llvm::BasicBlock *MergeBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("ifcont");
3227
3228 // if (lane_id == 0)
3229 llvm::Value *IsWarpMaster = Bld.CreateIsNull(LaneID, "warp_master");
3230 Bld.CreateCondBr(IsWarpMaster, ThenBB, ElseBB);
3231 CGF.EmitBlock(ThenBB);
3232
3233 // Reduce element = LocalReduceList[i]
3234 Address ElemPtrPtrAddr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(LocalReduceList, Idx);
3235 llvm::Value *ElemPtrPtr = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
3236 ElemPtrPtrAddr, /*Volatile=*/false, C.VoidPtrTy, SourceLocation());
3237 // elemptr = ((CopyType*)(elemptrptr)) + I
3238 Address ElemPtr = Address(ElemPtrPtr, Align);
3239 ElemPtr = Bld.CreateElementBitCast(ElemPtr, CopyType);
3240 if (NumIters > 1) {
3241 ElemPtr = Address(Bld.CreateGEP(ElemPtr.getPointer(), Cnt),
3242 ElemPtr.getAlignment());
3243 }
3244
3245 // Get pointer to location in transfer medium.
3246 // MediumPtr = &medium[warp_id]
3247 llvm::Value *MediumPtrVal = Bld.CreateInBoundsGEP(
3248 TransferMedium, {llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int64Ty), WarpID});
3249 Address MediumPtr(MediumPtrVal, Align);
3250 // Casting to actual data type.
3251 // MediumPtr = (CopyType*)MediumPtrAddr;
3252 MediumPtr = Bld.CreateElementBitCast(MediumPtr, CopyType);
3253
3254 // elem = *elemptr
3255 //*MediumPtr = elem
3256 llvm::Value *Elem =
3257 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(ElemPtr, /*Volatile=*/false, CType, Loc);
3258 // Store the source element value to the dest element address.
3259 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Elem, MediumPtr, /*Volatile=*/true, CType);
3260
3261 Bld.CreateBr(MergeBB);
3262
3263 CGF.EmitBlock(ElseBB);
3264 Bld.CreateBr(MergeBB);
3265
3266 CGF.EmitBlock(MergeBB);
3267
3268 // kmpc_barrier.
3269 CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().emitBarrierCall(CGF, Loc, OMPD_unknown,
3270 /*EmitChecks=*/false,
3271 /*ForceSimpleCall=*/true);
3272
3273 //
3274 // Warp 0 copies reduce element from transfer medium.
3275 //
3276 llvm::BasicBlock *W0ThenBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("then");
3277 llvm::BasicBlock *W0ElseBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("else");
3278 llvm::BasicBlock *W0MergeBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("ifcont");
3279
3280 Address AddrNumWarpsArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&NumWarpsArg);
3281 llvm::Value *NumWarpsVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
3282 AddrNumWarpsArg, /*Volatile=*/false, C.IntTy, Loc);
3283
3284 // Up to 32 threads in warp 0 are active.
3285 llvm::Value *IsActiveThread =
3286 Bld.CreateICmpULT(ThreadID, NumWarpsVal, "is_active_thread");
3287 Bld.CreateCondBr(IsActiveThread, W0ThenBB, W0ElseBB);
3288
3289 CGF.EmitBlock(W0ThenBB);
3290
3291 // SrcMediumPtr = &medium[tid]
3292 llvm::Value *SrcMediumPtrVal = Bld.CreateInBoundsGEP(
3293 TransferMedium,
3294 {llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int64Ty), ThreadID});
3295 Address SrcMediumPtr(SrcMediumPtrVal, Align);
3296 // SrcMediumVal = *SrcMediumPtr;
3297 SrcMediumPtr = Bld.CreateElementBitCast(SrcMediumPtr, CopyType);
3298
3299 // TargetElemPtr = (CopyType*)(SrcDataAddr[i]) + I
3300 Address TargetElemPtrPtr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(LocalReduceList, Idx);
3301 llvm::Value *TargetElemPtrVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
3302 TargetElemPtrPtr, /*Volatile=*/false, C.VoidPtrTy, Loc);
3303 Address TargetElemPtr = Address(TargetElemPtrVal, Align);
3304 TargetElemPtr = Bld.CreateElementBitCast(TargetElemPtr, CopyType);
3305 if (NumIters > 1) {
3306 TargetElemPtr = Address(Bld.CreateGEP(TargetElemPtr.getPointer(), Cnt),
3307 TargetElemPtr.getAlignment());
3308 }
3309
3310 // *TargetElemPtr = SrcMediumVal;
3311 llvm::Value *SrcMediumValue =
3312 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(SrcMediumPtr, /*Volatile=*/true, CType, Loc);
3313 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(SrcMediumValue, TargetElemPtr, /*Volatile=*/false,
3314 CType);
3315 Bld.CreateBr(W0MergeBB);
3316
3317 CGF.EmitBlock(W0ElseBB);
3318 Bld.CreateBr(W0MergeBB);
3319
3320 CGF.EmitBlock(W0MergeBB);
3321
3322 if (NumIters > 1) {
3323 Cnt = Bld.CreateNSWAdd(Cnt, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, /*V=*/1));
3324 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Cnt, CntAddr, /*Volatile=*/false, C.IntTy);
3325 CGF.EmitBranch(PrecondBB);
3326 (void)ApplyDebugLocation::CreateEmpty(CGF);
3327 CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB);
3328 }
3329 RealTySize %= TySize;
3330 }
3331 ++Idx;
3332 }
3333
3334 CGF.FinishFunction();
3335 return Fn;
3336}

3338/// Emit a helper that reduces data across two OpenMP threads (lanes)
3339/// in the same warp. It uses shuffle instructions to copy over data from
3340/// a remote lane's stack. The reduction algorithm performed is specified
3341/// by the fourth parameter.
3342///
3343/// Algorithm Versions.
3344/// Full Warp Reduce (argument value 0):
3345/// This algorithm assumes that all 32 lanes are active and gathers
3346/// data from these 32 lanes, producing a single resultant value.
3347/// Contiguous Partial Warp Reduce (argument value 1):
3348/// This algorithm assumes that only a *contiguous* subset of lanes
3349/// are active. This happens for the last warp in a parallel region
3350/// when the user specified num_threads is not an integer multiple of
3351/// 32. This contiguous subset always starts with the zeroth lane.
3352/// Partial Warp Reduce (argument value 2):
3353/// This algorithm gathers data from any number of lanes at any position.
3354/// All reduced values are stored in the lowest possible lane. The set
3355/// of problems every algorithm addresses is a super set of those
3356/// addressable by algorithms with a lower version number. Overhead
3357/// increases as algorithm version increases.
3358///
3359/// Terminology
3360/// Reduce element:
3361/// Reduce element refers to the individual data field with primitive
3362/// data types to be combined and reduced across threads.
3363/// Reduce list:
3364/// Reduce list refers to a collection of local, thread-private
3365/// reduce elements.
3366/// Remote Reduce list:
3367/// Remote Reduce list refers to a collection of remote (relative to
3368/// the current thread) reduce elements.
3369///
3370/// We distinguish between three states of threads that are important to
3371/// the implementation of this function.
3372/// Alive threads:
3373/// Threads in a warp executing the SIMT instruction, as distinguished from
3374/// threads that are inactive due to divergent control flow.
3375/// Active threads:
3376/// The minimal set of threads that has to be alive upon entry to this
3377/// function. The computation is correct iff active threads are alive.
3378/// Some threads are alive but they are not active because they do not
3379/// contribute to the computation in any useful manner. Turning them off
3380/// may introduce control flow overheads without any tangible benefits.
3381/// Effective threads:
3382/// In order to comply with the argument requirements of the shuffle
3383/// function, we must keep all lanes holding data alive. But at most
3384/// half of them perform value aggregation; we refer to this half of
3385/// threads as effective. The other half is simply handing off their
3386/// data.
3387///
3388/// Procedure
3389/// Value shuffle:
3390/// In this step active threads transfer data from higher lane positions
3391/// in the warp to lower lane positions, creating Remote Reduce list.
3392/// Value aggregation:
3393/// In this step, effective threads combine their thread local Reduce list
3394/// with Remote Reduce list and store the result in the thread local
3395/// Reduce list.
3396/// Value copy:
3397/// In this step, we deal with the assumption made by algorithm 2
3398/// (i.e. contiguity assumption). When we have an odd number of lanes
3399/// active, say 2k+1, only k threads will be effective and therefore k
3400/// new values will be produced. However, the Reduce list owned by the
3401/// (2k+1)th thread is ignored in the value aggregation. Therefore
3402/// we copy the Reduce list from the (2k+1)th lane to (k+1)th lane so
3403/// that the contiguity assumption still holds.
3404static llvm::Function *emitShuffleAndReduceFunction(
3405 CodeGenModule &CGM, ArrayRef<const Expr *> Privates,
3406 QualType ReductionArrayTy, llvm::Function *ReduceFn, SourceLocation Loc) {
3407 ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
3408
3409 // Thread local Reduce list used to host the values of data to be reduced.
3410 ImplicitParamDecl ReduceListArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3411 C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3412 // Current lane id; could be logical.
3413 ImplicitParamDecl LaneIDArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr, C.ShortTy,
3414 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3415 // Offset of the remote source lane relative to the current lane.
3416 ImplicitParamDecl RemoteLaneOffsetArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3417 C.ShortTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3418 // Algorithm version. This is expected to be known at compile time.
3419 ImplicitParamDecl AlgoVerArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3420 C.ShortTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3421 FunctionArgList Args;
3422 Args.push_back(&ReduceListArg);
3423 Args.push_back(&LaneIDArg);
3424 Args.push_back(&RemoteLaneOffsetArg);
3425 Args.push_back(&AlgoVerArg);
3426
3427 const CGFunctionInfo &CGFI =
3428 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(C.VoidTy, Args);
3429 auto *Fn = llvm::Function::Create(
3430 CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(CGFI), llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
3431 "_omp_reduction_shuffle_and_reduce_func", &CGM.getModule());
3432 CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, CGFI);
3433 Fn->setDoesNotRecurse();
3434 if (CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize) {
3435 Fn->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
3436 Fn->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeNone);
3437 Fn->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
3438 }
3439
3440 CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
3441 CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), C.VoidTy, Fn, CGFI, Args, Loc, Loc);
3442
3443 CGBuilderTy &Bld = CGF.Builder;
3444
3445 Address AddrReduceListArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ReduceListArg);
3446 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
3447 Address LocalReduceList(
3448 Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3449 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(AddrReduceListArg, /*Volatile=*/false,
3450 C.VoidPtrTy, SourceLocation()),
3451 CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ReductionArrayTy)->getPointerTo(DefaultAS)),
3452 CGF.getPointerAlign());
3453
3454 Address AddrLaneIDArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&LaneIDArg);
3455 llvm::Value *LaneIDArgVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
3456 AddrLaneIDArg, /*Volatile=*/false, C.ShortTy, SourceLocation());
3457
3458 Address AddrRemoteLaneOffsetArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&RemoteLaneOffsetArg);
3459 llvm::Value *RemoteLaneOffsetArgVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
3460 AddrRemoteLaneOffsetArg, /*Volatile=*/false, C.ShortTy, SourceLocation());
3461
3462 Address AddrAlgoVerArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&AlgoVerArg);
3463 llvm::Value *AlgoVerArgVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
3464 AddrAlgoVerArg, /*Volatile=*/false, C.ShortTy, SourceLocation());
3465
3466 // Create a local thread-private variable to host the Reduce list
3467 // from a remote lane.
3468 Address RemoteReduceList =
3469 CGF.CreateMemTemp(ReductionArrayTy, ".omp.reduction.remote_reduce_list");
3470
3471 // This loop iterates through the list of reduce elements and copies,
3472 // element by element, from a remote lane in the warp to RemoteReduceList,
3473 // hosted on the thread's stack.
3474 emitReductionListCopy(RemoteLaneToThread, CGF, ReductionArrayTy, Privates,
3475 LocalReduceList, RemoteReduceList,
3476 {/*RemoteLaneOffset=*/RemoteLaneOffsetArgVal,
3477 /*ScratchpadIndex=*/nullptr,
3478 /*ScratchpadWidth=*/nullptr});
3479
3480 // The actions to be performed on the Remote Reduce list is dependent
3481 // on the algorithm version.
3482 //
3483 // if (AlgoVer==0) || (AlgoVer==1 && (LaneId < Offset)) || (AlgoVer==2 &&
3484 // LaneId % 2 == 0 && Offset > 0):
3485 // do the reduction value aggregation
3486 //
3487 // The thread local variable Reduce list is mutated in place to host the
3488 // reduced data, which is the aggregated value produced from local and
3489 // remote lanes.
3490 //
3491 // Note that AlgoVer is expected to be a constant integer known at compile
3492 // time.
3493 // When AlgoVer==0, the first conjunction evaluates to true, making
3494 // the entire predicate true during compile time.
3495 // When AlgoVer==1, the second conjunction has only the second part to be
3496 // evaluated during runtime. Other conjunctions evaluates to false
3497 // during compile time.
3498 // When AlgoVer==2, the third conjunction has only the second part to be
3499 // evaluated during runtime. Other conjunctions evaluates to false
3500 // during compile time.
3501 llvm::Value *CondAlgo0 = Bld.CreateIsNull(AlgoVerArgVal);
3502
3503 llvm::Value *Algo1 = Bld.CreateICmpEQ(AlgoVerArgVal, Bld.getInt16(1));
3504 llvm::Value *CondAlgo1 = Bld.CreateAnd(
3505 Algo1, Bld.CreateICmpULT(LaneIDArgVal, RemoteLaneOffsetArgVal));
3506
3507 llvm::Value *Algo2 = Bld.CreateICmpEQ(AlgoVerArgVal, Bld.getInt16(2));
3508 llvm::Value *CondAlgo2 = Bld.CreateAnd(
3509 Algo2, Bld.CreateIsNull(Bld.CreateAnd(LaneIDArgVal, Bld.getInt16(1))));
3510 CondAlgo2 = Bld.CreateAnd(
3511 CondAlgo2, Bld.CreateICmpSGT(RemoteLaneOffsetArgVal, Bld.getInt16(0)));
3512
3513 llvm::Value *CondReduce = Bld.CreateOr(CondAlgo0, CondAlgo1);
3514 CondReduce = Bld.CreateOr(CondReduce, CondAlgo2);
3515
3516 llvm::BasicBlock *ThenBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("then");
3517 llvm::BasicBlock *ElseBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("else");
3518 llvm::BasicBlock *MergeBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("ifcont");
3519 Bld.CreateCondBr(CondReduce, ThenBB, ElseBB);
3520
3521 CGF.EmitBlock(ThenBB);
3522 // reduce_function(LocalReduceList, RemoteReduceList)
3523 llvm::Value *LocalReduceListPtr = Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3524 LocalReduceList.getPointer(), CGF.VoidPtrTy);
3525 llvm::Value *RemoteReduceListPtr = Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3526 RemoteReduceList.getPointer(), CGF.VoidPtrTy);
3527 CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().emitOutlinedFunctionCall(
3528 CGF, Loc, ReduceFn, {LocalReduceListPtr, RemoteReduceListPtr});
3529 Bld.CreateBr(MergeBB);
3530
3531 CGF.EmitBlock(ElseBB);
3532 Bld.CreateBr(MergeBB);
3533
3534 CGF.EmitBlock(MergeBB);
3535
3536 // if (AlgoVer==1 && (LaneId >= Offset)) copy Remote Reduce list to local
3537 // Reduce list.
3538 Algo1 = Bld.CreateICmpEQ(AlgoVerArgVal, Bld.getInt16(1));
3539 llvm::Value *CondCopy = Bld.CreateAnd(
3540 Algo1, Bld.CreateICmpUGE(LaneIDArgVal, RemoteLaneOffsetArgVal));
3541
3542 llvm::BasicBlock *CpyThenBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("then");
3543 llvm::BasicBlock *CpyElseBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("else");
3544 llvm::BasicBlock *CpyMergeBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("ifcont");
3545 Bld.CreateCondBr(CondCopy, CpyThenBB, CpyElseBB);
3546
3547 CGF.EmitBlock(CpyThenBB);
3548 emitReductionListCopy(ThreadCopy, CGF, ReductionArrayTy, Privates,
3549 RemoteReduceList, LocalReduceList);
3550 Bld.CreateBr(CpyMergeBB);
3551
3552 CGF.EmitBlock(CpyElseBB);
3553 Bld.CreateBr(CpyMergeBB);
3554
3555 CGF.EmitBlock(CpyMergeBB);
3556
3557 CGF.FinishFunction();
3558 return Fn;
3559}

3561/// This function emits a helper that copies all the reduction variables from
3562/// the team into the provided global buffer for the reduction variables.
3563///
3564/// void list_to_global_copy_func(void *buffer, int Idx, void *reduce_data)
3565/// For all data entries D in reduce_data:
3566/// Copy local D to buffer.D[Idx]
3567static llvm::Value *emitListToGlobalCopyFunction(
3568 CodeGenModule &CGM, ArrayRef<const Expr *> Privates,
3569 QualType ReductionArrayTy, SourceLocation Loc,
3570 const RecordDecl *TeamReductionRec,
3571 const llvm::SmallDenseMap<const ValueDecl *, const FieldDecl *>
3572 &VarFieldMap) {
3573 ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
3574
3575 // Buffer: global reduction buffer.
3576 ImplicitParamDecl BufferArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3577 C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3578 // Idx: index of the buffer.
3579 ImplicitParamDecl IdxArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr, C.IntTy,
3580 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3581 // ReduceList: thread local Reduce list.
3582 ImplicitParamDecl ReduceListArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3583 C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3584 FunctionArgList Args;
3585 Args.push_back(&BufferArg);
3586 Args.push_back(&IdxArg);
3587 Args.push_back(&ReduceListArg);
3588
3589 const CGFunctionInfo &CGFI =
3590 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(C.VoidTy, Args);
3591 auto *Fn = llvm::Function::Create(
3592 CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(CGFI), llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
3593 "_omp_reduction_list_to_global_copy_func", &CGM.getModule());
3594 CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, CGFI);
3595 Fn->setDoesNotRecurse();
3596 CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
3597 CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), C.VoidTy, Fn, CGFI, Args, Loc, Loc);
3598
3599 CGBuilderTy &Bld = CGF.Builder;
3600
3601 Address AddrReduceListArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ReduceListArg);
3602 Address AddrBufferArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&BufferArg);
3603 Address LocalReduceList(
3604 Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3605 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(AddrReduceListArg, /*Volatile=*/false,
3606 C.VoidPtrTy, Loc),
3607 CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ReductionArrayTy)->getPointerTo()),
3608 CGF.getPointerAlign());
3609 QualType StaticTy = C.getRecordType(TeamReductionRec);
3610 llvm::Type *LLVMReductionsBufferTy =
3611 CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(StaticTy);
3612 llvm::Value *BufferArrPtr = Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3613 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(AddrBufferArg, /*Volatile=*/false, C.VoidPtrTy, Loc),
3614 LLVMReductionsBufferTy->getPointerTo());
3615 llvm::Value *Idxs[] = {llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(CGF.Int32Ty),
3616 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&IdxArg),
3617 /*Volatile=*/false, C.IntTy,
3618 Loc)};
3619 unsigned Idx = 0;
3620 for (const Expr *Private : Privates) {
3621 // Reduce element = LocalReduceList[i]
3622 Address ElemPtrPtrAddr = Bld.CreateConstArrayGEP(LocalReduceList, Idx);
3623 llvm::Value *ElemPtrPtr = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
3624 ElemPtrPtrAddr, /*Volatile=*/false, C.VoidPtrTy, SourceLocation());
3625 // elemptr = ((CopyType*)(elemptrptr)) + I
3626 ElemPtrPtr = Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3627 ElemPtrPtr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Private->getType())->getPointerTo());
3628 Address ElemPtr =
3629 Address(ElemPtrPtr, C.getTypeAlignInChars(Private->getType()));
3630 const ValueDecl *VD = cast<DeclRefExpr>(Private)->getDecl();
3631 // Global = Buffer.VD[Idx];
3632 const FieldDecl *FD = VarFieldMap.lookup(VD);
3633 LValue GlobLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(
3634 CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(BufferArrPtr, StaticTy), FD);
3635 llvm::Value *BufferPtr = Bld.CreateInBoundsGEP(GlobLVal.getPointer(), Idxs);
3636 GlobLVal.setAddress(Address(BufferPtr, GlobLVal.getAlignment()));
3637 switch (CGF.getEvaluationKind(Private->getType())) {
3638 case TEK_Scalar: {
3639 llvm::Value *V = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(ElemPtr, /*Volatile=*/false,
3640 Private->getType(), Loc);
3641 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(V, GlobLVal);
3642 break;
3643 }
3644 case TEK_Complex: {
3645 CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy V = CGF.EmitLoadOfComplex(
3646 CGF.MakeAddrLValue(ElemPtr, Private->getType()), Loc);
3647 CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(V, GlobLVal, /*isInit=*/false);
3648 break;
3649 }
3650 case TEK_Aggregate:
3651 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(GlobLVal,
3652 CGF.MakeAddrLValue(ElemPtr, Private->getType()),
3653 Private->getType(), AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap);
3654 break;
3655 }
3656 ++Idx;
3657 }
3658
3659 CGF.FinishFunction();
3660 return Fn;
3661}

3663/// This function emits a helper that reduces all the reduction variables from
3664/// the team into the provided global buffer for the reduction variables.
3665///
3666/// void list_to_global_reduce_func(void *buffer, int Idx, void *reduce_data)
3667/// void *GlobPtrs[];
3668/// GlobPtrs[0] = (void*)&buffer.D0[Idx];
3669/// ...
3670/// GlobPtrs[N] = (void*)&buffer.DN[Idx];
3671/// reduce_function(GlobPtrs, reduce_data);
3672static llvm::Value *emitListToGlobalReduceFunction(
3673 CodeGenModule &CGM, ArrayRef<const Expr *> Privates,
3674 QualType ReductionArrayTy, SourceLocation Loc,
3675 const RecordDecl *TeamReductionRec,
3676 const llvm::SmallDenseMap<const ValueDecl *, const FieldDecl *>
3677 &VarFieldMap,
3678 llvm::Function *ReduceFn) {

3680
3681 // Buffer: global reduction buffer.
3682 ImplicitParamDecl BufferArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3683 C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3684 // Idx: index of the buffer.
3685 ImplicitParamDecl IdxArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr, C.IntTy,
3686 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3687 // ReduceList: thread local Reduce list.
3688 ImplicitParamDecl ReduceListArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
3689 C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3690 FunctionArgList Args;
3691 Args.push_back(&BufferArg);
3692 Args.push_back(&IdxArg);
3693 Args.push_back(&ReduceListArg);
3694
3695 const CGFunctionInfo &CGFI =
3696 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(C.VoidTy, Args);
3697 auto *Fn = llvm::Function::Create(
3698 CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(CGFI), llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
3699 "_omp_reduction_list_to_global_reduce_func", &CGM.getModule());
3700 CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, CGFI);
3701 Fn->setDoesNotRecurse();
3702 CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
3703 CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), C.VoidTy, Fn, CGFI, Args, Loc, Loc);
3704
3705 CGBuilderTy &Bld = CGF.Builder;
3706
3707 Address AddrBufferArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&BufferArg);
3708 QualType StaticTy = C.getRecordType(TeamReductionRec);
3709 llvm::Type *LLVMReductionsBufferTy =
3710 CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(StaticTy);
3711 llvm::Value *BufferArrPtr = Bld.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3712 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(AddrBufferArg, /*Volatile=*/false, C.VoidPtrTy, Loc),
3713 LLVMReductionsBufferTy->getPointerTo());
3714
3715 // 1. Build a list of reduction variables.
3716 // void *RedList[<n>] = {<ReductionVars>[0], ..., <ReductionVars>[<n>-1]};
3717 Address ReductionList =
3718 CGF.CreateMemTemp(ReductionArrayTy, ".omp.reduction.red_list");
3719 auto IPriv = Privates.begin();
3720 llvm::Value *Idxs[] = {llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(CGF.Int32Ty),
3721 CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&IdxArg),
3722 /*Volatile=*/false, C.IntTy,
3723 Loc)};
3724 unsigned Idx = 0;
3725 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Privates.size(); I < E; ++I, ++IPriv, ++Idx) {
3726 Address Elem = CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(ReductionList, Idx);
3727 // Global = Buffer.VD[Idx];
3728 const ValueDecl *VD = cast<DeclRefExpr>(*IPriv)->getDecl();
3729 const FieldDecl *FD = VarFieldMap.lookup(VD);
3730 LValue GlobLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(
3731 CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(BufferArrPtr, StaticTy), FD);
3732 llvm::Value *BufferPtr = Bld.CreateInBoundsGEP(GlobLVal.getPointer(), Idxs);
3733 llvm::Value *Ptr = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(BufferPtr);
3734 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Ptr, Elem, /*Volatile=*/false, C.VoidPtrTy);
3735 if ((*IPriv)->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType()) {
3736 // Store array size.
3737 ++Idx;
3738 Elem = CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(ReductionList, Idx);
3739 llvm::Value *Size = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
3740 CGF.getVLASize(
3741 CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType((*IPriv)->getType()))
3742 .NumElts,
3743 CGF.SizeTy, /*isSigned=*/false);
3744 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Size, CGF.VoidPtrTy),
3745 Elem);
3746 }
3747 }
3748
3749 // Call reduce_function(GlobalReduceList, ReduceList)
3750 llvm::Value *GlobalReduceList =
3751 CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(ReductionList.getPointer());
3752 Address AddrReduceListArg = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ReduceListArg);
3753 llvm::Value *ReducedPtr = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
3754 AddrReduceListArg, /*Volatile=*/false, C.VoidPtrTy, Loc);
3755 CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().emitOutlinedFunctionCall(
3756 CGF, Loc, ReduceFn, {GlobalReduceList, ReducedPtr});
3757 CGF.FinishFunction();
3758 return Fn;
3759}

3961///
3962/// Design of OpenMP reductions on the GPU
3963///
3964/// Consider a typical OpenMP program with one or more reduction
3965/// clauses:
3966///
3967/// float foo;
3968/// double bar;
3969/// #pragma omp target teams distribute parallel for \
3970/// reduction(+:foo) reduction(*:bar)
3971/// for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
3972/// foo += A[i]; bar *= B[i];
3973/// }
3974///
3975/// where 'foo' and 'bar' are reduced across all OpenMP threads in
3976/// all teams. In our OpenMP implementation on the NVPTX device an
3977/// OpenMP team is mapped to a CUDA threadblock and OpenMP threads
3978/// within a team are mapped to CUDA threads within a threadblock.
3979/// Our goal is to efficiently aggregate values across all OpenMP
3980/// threads such that:
3981///
3982/// - the compiler and runtime are logically concise, and
3983/// - the reduction is performed efficiently in a hierarchical
3984/// manner as follows: within OpenMP threads in the same warp,
3985/// across warps in a threadblock, and finally across teams on
3986/// the NVPTX device.
3987///
3988/// Introduction to Decoupling
3989///
3990/// We would like to decouple the compiler and the runtime so that the
3991/// latter is ignorant of the reduction variables (number, data types)
3992/// and the reduction operators. This allows a simpler interface
3993/// and implementation while still attaining good performance.
3994///
3995/// Pseudocode for the aforementioned OpenMP program generated by the
3996/// compiler is as follows:
3997///
3998/// 1. Create private copies of reduction variables on each OpenMP
3999/// thread: 'foo_private', 'bar_private'
4000/// 2. Each OpenMP thread reduces the chunk of 'A' and 'B' assigned
4001/// to it and writes the result in 'foo_private' and 'bar_private'
4002/// respectively.
4003/// 3. Call the OpenMP runtime on the GPU to reduce within a team
4004/// and store the result on the team master:
4005///
4006/// __kmpc_nvptx_parallel_reduce_nowait_v2(...,
4007/// reduceData, shuffleReduceFn, interWarpCpyFn)
4008///
4009/// where:
4010/// struct ReduceData {
4011/// double *foo;
4012/// double *bar;
4013/// } reduceData
4014/// reduceData.foo = &foo_private
4015/// reduceData.bar = &bar_private
4016///
4017/// 'shuffleReduceFn' and 'interWarpCpyFn' are pointers to two
4018/// auxiliary functions generated by the compiler that operate on
4019/// variables of type 'ReduceData'. They aid the runtime perform
4020/// algorithmic steps in a data agnostic manner.
4021///
4022/// 'shuffleReduceFn' is a pointer to a function that reduces data
4023/// of type 'ReduceData' across two OpenMP threads (lanes) in the
4024/// same warp. It takes the following arguments as input:
4025///
4026/// a. variable of type 'ReduceData' on the calling lane,
4027/// b. its lane_id,
4028/// c. an offset relative to the current lane_id to generate a
4029/// remote_lane_id. The remote lane contains the second
4030/// variable of type 'ReduceData' that is to be reduced.
4031/// d. an algorithm version parameter determining which reduction
4032/// algorithm to use.
4033///
4034/// 'shuffleReduceFn' retrieves data from the remote lane using
4035/// efficient GPU shuffle intrinsics and reduces, using the
4036/// algorithm specified by the 4th parameter, the two operands
4037/// element-wise. The result is written to the first operand.
4038///
4039/// Different reduction algorithms are implemented in different
4040/// runtime functions, all calling 'shuffleReduceFn' to perform
4041/// the essential reduction step. Therefore, based on the 4th
4042/// parameter, this function behaves slightly differently to
4043/// cooperate with the runtime to ensure correctness under
4044/// different circumstances.
4045///
4046/// 'InterWarpCpyFn' is a pointer to a function that transfers
4047/// reduced variables across warps. It tunnels, through CUDA
4048/// shared memory, the thread-private data of type 'ReduceData'
4049/// from lane 0 of each warp to a lane in the first warp.
4050/// 4. Call the OpenMP runtime on the GPU to reduce across teams.
4051/// The last team writes the global reduced value to memory.
4052///
4053/// ret = __kmpc_nvptx_teams_reduce_nowait(...,
4054/// reduceData, shuffleReduceFn, interWarpCpyFn,
4055/// scratchpadCopyFn, loadAndReduceFn)
4056///
4057/// 'scratchpadCopyFn' is a helper that stores reduced
4058/// data from the team master to a scratchpad array in
4059/// global memory.
4060///
4061/// 'loadAndReduceFn' is a helper that loads data from
4062/// the scratchpad array and reduces it with the input
4063/// operand.
4064///
4065/// These compiler generated functions hide address
4066/// calculation and alignment information from the runtime.
4067/// 5. if ret == 1:
4068/// The team master of the last team stores the reduced
4069/// result to the globals in memory.
4070/// foo += reduceData.foo; bar *= reduceData.bar
4071///
4072///
4073/// Warp Reduction Algorithms
4074///
4075/// On the warp level, we have three algorithms implemented in the
4076/// OpenMP runtime depending on the number of active lanes:
4077///
4078/// Full Warp Reduction
4079///
4080/// The reduce algorithm within a warp where all lanes are active
4081/// is implemented in the runtime as follows:
4082///
4083/// full_warp_reduce(void *reduce_data,
4084/// kmp_ShuffleReductFctPtr ShuffleReduceFn) {
4085/// for (int offset = WARPSIZE/2; offset > 0; offset /= 2)
4086/// ShuffleReduceFn(reduce_data, 0, offset, 0);
4087/// }
4088///
4089/// The algorithm completes in log(2, WARPSIZE) steps.
4090///
4091/// 'ShuffleReduceFn' is used here with lane_id set to 0 because it is
4092/// not used therefore we save instructions by not retrieving lane_id
4093/// from the corresponding special registers. The 4th parameter, which
4094/// represents the version of the algorithm being used, is set to 0 to
4095/// signify full warp reduction.
4096///
4097/// In this version, 'ShuffleReduceFn' behaves, per element, as follows:
4098///
4099/// #reduce_elem refers to an element in the local lane's data structure
4100/// #remote_elem is retrieved from a remote lane
4101/// remote_elem = shuffle_down(reduce_elem, offset, WARPSIZE);
4102/// reduce_elem = reduce_elem REDUCE_OP remote_elem;
4103///
4104/// Contiguous Partial Warp Reduction
4105///
4106/// This reduce algorithm is used within a warp where only the first
4107/// 'n' (n <= WARPSIZE) lanes are active. It is typically used when the
4108/// number of OpenMP threads in a parallel region is not a multiple of
4109/// WARPSIZE. The algorithm is implemented in the runtime as follows:
4110///
4111/// void
4112/// contiguous_partial_reduce(void *reduce_data,
4113/// kmp_ShuffleReductFctPtr ShuffleReduceFn,
4114/// int size, int lane_id) {
4115/// int curr_size;
4116/// int offset;
4117/// curr_size = size;
4118/// mask = curr_size/2;
4119/// while (offset>0) {
4120/// ShuffleReduceFn(reduce_data, lane_id, offset, 1);
4121/// curr_size = (curr_size+1)/2;
4122/// offset = curr_size/2;
4123/// }
4124/// }
4125///
4126/// In this version, 'ShuffleReduceFn' behaves, per element, as follows:
4127///
4128/// remote_elem = shuffle_down(reduce_elem, offset, WARPSIZE);
4129/// if (lane_id < offset)
4130/// reduce_elem = reduce_elem REDUCE_OP remote_elem
4131/// else
4132/// reduce_elem = remote_elem
4133///
4134/// This algorithm assumes that the data to be reduced are located in a
4135/// contiguous subset of lanes starting from the first. When there is
4136/// an odd number of active lanes, the data in the last lane is not
4137/// aggregated with any other lane's dat but is instead copied over.
4138///
4139/// Dispersed Partial Warp Reduction
4140///
4141/// This algorithm is used within a warp when any discontiguous subset of
4142/// lanes are active. It is used to implement the reduction operation
4143/// across lanes in an OpenMP simd region or in a nested parallel region.
4144///
4145/// void
4146/// dispersed_partial_reduce(void *reduce_data,
4147/// kmp_ShuffleReductFctPtr ShuffleReduceFn) {
4148/// int size, remote_id;
4149/// int logical_lane_id = number_of_active_lanes_before_me() * 2;
4150/// do {
4151/// remote_id = next_active_lane_id_right_after_me();
4152/// # the above function returns 0 of no active lane
4153/// # is present right after the current lane.
4154/// size = number_of_active_lanes_in_this_warp();
4155/// logical_lane_id /= 2;
4156/// ShuffleReduceFn(reduce_data, logical_lane_id,
4157/// remote_id-1-threadIdx.x, 2);
4158/// } while (logical_lane_id % 2 == 0 && size > 1);
4159/// }
4160///
4161/// There is no assumption made about the initial state of the reduction.
4162/// Any number of lanes (>=1) could be active at any position. The reduction
4163/// result is returned in the first active lane.
4164///
4165/// In this version, 'ShuffleReduceFn' behaves, per element, as follows:
4166///
4167/// remote_elem = shuffle_down(reduce_elem, offset, WARPSIZE);
4168/// if (lane_id % 2 == 0 && offset > 0)
4169/// reduce_elem = reduce_elem REDUCE_OP remote_elem
4170/// else
4171/// reduce_elem = remote_elem
4172///
4173///
4174/// Intra-Team Reduction
4175///
4176/// This function, as implemented in the runtime call
4177/// '__kmpc_nvptx_parallel_reduce_nowait_v2', aggregates data across OpenMP
4178/// threads in a team. It first reduces within a warp using the
4179/// aforementioned algorithms. We then proceed to gather all such
4180/// reduced values at the first warp.
4181///
4182/// The runtime makes use of the function 'InterWarpCpyFn', which copies
4183/// data from each of the "warp master" (zeroth lane of each warp, where
4184/// warp-reduced data is held) to the zeroth warp. This step reduces (in
4185/// a mathematical sense) the problem of reduction across warp masters in
4186/// a block to the problem of warp reduction.
4187///
4188///
4189/// Inter-Team Reduction
4190///
4191/// Once a team has reduced its data to a single value, it is stored in
4192/// a global scratchpad array. Since each team has a distinct slot, this
4193/// can be done without locking.
4194///
4195/// The last team to write to the scratchpad array proceeds to reduce the
4196/// scratchpad array. One or more workers in the last team use the helper
4197/// 'loadAndReduceDataFn' to load and reduce values from the array, i.e.,
4198/// the k'th worker reduces every k'th element.
4199///
4200/// Finally, a call is made to '__kmpc_nvptx_parallel_reduce_nowait_v2' to
4201/// reduce across workers and compute a globally reduced value.
4202///
4203void CGOpenMPRuntimeNVPTX::emitReduction(
4204 CodeGenFunction &CGF, SourceLocation Loc, ArrayRef<const Expr *> Privates,
4205 ArrayRef<const Expr *> LHSExprs, ArrayRef<const Expr *> RHSExprs,
4206 ArrayRef<const Expr *> ReductionOps, ReductionOptionsTy Options) {
4207 if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
4208 return;
4209
4210 bool ParallelReduction = isOpenMPParallelDirective(Options.ReductionKind);
4211#ifndef NDEBUG
4212 bool TeamsReduction = isOpenMPTeamsDirective(Options.ReductionKind);
4213#endif
4214
4215 if (Options.SimpleReduction) {
4216 assert(!TeamsReduction && !ParallelReduction &&
4217 "Invalid reduction selection in emitReduction.");
4218 CGOpenMPRuntime::emitReduction(CGF, Loc, Privates, LHSExprs, RHSExprs,
4219 ReductionOps, Options);
4220 return;
4221 }
4222
4223 assert((TeamsReduction || ParallelReduction) &&
4224 "Invalid reduction selection in emitReduction.");
4225
4226 // Build res = __kmpc_reduce{_nowait}(<gtid>, <n>, sizeof(RedList),
4227 // RedList, shuffle_reduce_func, interwarp_copy_func);
4228 // or
4229 // Build res = __kmpc_reduce_teams_nowait_simple(<loc>, <gtid>, <lck>);
4230 llvm::Value *RTLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc);
4231 llvm::Value *ThreadId = getThreadID(CGF, Loc);
4232
4233 llvm::Value *Res;
4234 ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
4235 // 1. Build a list of reduction variables.
4236 // void *RedList[<n>] = {<ReductionVars>[0], ..., <ReductionVars>[<n>-1]};
4237 auto Size = RHSExprs.size();
4238 for (const Expr *E : Privates) {
4239 if (E->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType())
4240 // Reserve place for array size.
4241 ++Size;
4242 }
4243 llvm::APInt ArraySize(/*unsigned int numBits=*/32, Size);
4244 QualType ReductionArrayTy =
4245 C.getConstantArrayType(C.VoidPtrTy, ArraySize, ArrayType::Normal,
4246 /*IndexTypeQuals=*/0);
4247 Address ReductionList =
4248 CGF.CreateMemTemp(ReductionArrayTy, ".omp.reduction.red_list");
4249 auto IPriv = Privates.begin();
4250 unsigned Idx = 0;
4251 for (unsigned I = 0, E = RHSExprs.size(); I < E; ++I, ++IPriv, ++Idx) {
4252 Address Elem = CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(ReductionList, Idx);
4253 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(
4254 CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
4255 CGF.EmitLValue(RHSExprs[I]).getPointer(), CGF.VoidPtrTy),
4256 Elem);
4257 if ((*IPriv)->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType()) {
4258 // Store array size.
4259 ++Idx;
4260 Elem = CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(ReductionList, Idx);
4261 llvm::Value *Size = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
4262 CGF.getVLASize(
4263 CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType((*IPriv)->getType()))
4264 .NumElts,
4265 CGF.SizeTy, /*isSigned=*/false);
4266 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Size, CGF.VoidPtrTy),
4267 Elem);
4268 }
4269 }
4270
4271 llvm::Value *RL = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
4272 ReductionList.getPointer(), CGF.VoidPtrTy);
4273 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
4274 llvm::Function *ReductionFn = emitReductionFunction(
4275 Loc, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ReductionArrayTy)->getPointerTo(DefaultAS), Privates,
4276 LHSExprs, RHSExprs, ReductionOps);
4277 llvm::Value *ReductionArrayTySize = CGF.getTypeSize(ReductionArrayTy);
4278 llvm::Function *ShuffleAndReduceFn = emitShuffleAndReduceFunction(
4279 CGM, Privates, ReductionArrayTy, ReductionFn, Loc);
4280 llvm::Value *InterWarpCopyFn =
4281 emitInterWarpCopyFunction(CGM, Privates, ReductionArrayTy, Loc);
4282
4283 if (ParallelReduction) {
4284 llvm::Value *Args[] = {RTLoc,
4285 ThreadId,
4286 CGF.Builder.getInt32(RHSExprs.size()),
4287 ReductionArrayTySize,
4288 RL,
4289 ShuffleAndReduceFn,
4290 InterWarpCopyFn};
4291
4292 Res = CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
4293 createNVPTXRuntimeFunction(
4294 OMPRTL_NVPTX__kmpc_nvptx_parallel_reduce_nowait_v2),
4295 Args);
4296 } else {
4297 assert(TeamsReduction && "expected teams reduction.");
4298 llvm::SmallDenseMap<const ValueDecl *, const FieldDecl *> VarFieldMap;
4299 llvm::SmallVector<const ValueDecl *, 4> PrivatesReductions(Privates.size());
4300 int Cnt = 0;
4301 for (const Expr *DRE : Privates) {
4302 PrivatesReductions[Cnt] = cast<DeclRefExpr>(DRE)->getDecl();
4303 ++Cnt;
4304 }
4305 const RecordDecl *TeamReductionRec = ::buildRecordForGlobalizedVars(
4306 CGM.getContext(), PrivatesReductions, llvm::None, VarFieldMap,
4307 C.getLangOpts().OpenMPCUDAReductionBufNum);
4308 TeamsReductions.push_back(TeamReductionRec);
4309 if (!KernelTeamsReductionPtr) {
4310 KernelTeamsReductionPtr = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
4311 CGM.getModule(), CGM.VoidPtrTy, /*isConstant=*/true,
4312 llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, nullptr,
4313 "_openmp_teams_reductions_buffer_$_$ptr");
4314 }
4315 llvm::Value *GlobalBufferPtr = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
4316 Address(KernelTeamsReductionPtr, CGM.getPointerAlign()),
4317 /*Volatile=*/false, C.getPointerType(C.VoidPtrTy), Loc);
4318 llvm::Value *GlobalToBufferCpyFn = ::emitListToGlobalCopyFunction(
4319 CGM, Privates, ReductionArrayTy, Loc, TeamReductionRec, VarFieldMap);
4320 llvm::Value *GlobalToBufferRedFn = ::emitListToGlobalReduceFunction(
4321 CGM, Privates, ReductionArrayTy, Loc, TeamReductionRec, VarFieldMap,
4322 ReductionFn);
4323 llvm::Value *BufferToGlobalCpyFn = ::emitGlobalToListCopyFunction(
4324 CGM, Privates, ReductionArrayTy, Loc, TeamReductionRec, VarFieldMap);
4325 llvm::Value *BufferToGlobalRedFn = ::emitGlobalToListReduceFunction(
4326 CGM, Privates, ReductionArrayTy, Loc, TeamReductionRec, VarFieldMap,
4327 ReductionFn);
4328
4329 llvm::Value *Args[] = {
4330 RTLoc,
4331 ThreadId,
4332 GlobalBufferPtr,
4333 CGF.Builder.getInt32(C.getLangOpts().OpenMPCUDAReductionBufNum),
4334 RL,
4335 ShuffleAndReduceFn,
4336 InterWarpCopyFn,
4337 GlobalToBufferCpyFn,
4338 GlobalToBufferRedFn,
4339 BufferToGlobalCpyFn,
4340 BufferToGlobalRedFn};
4341
4342 Res = CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
4343 createNVPTXRuntimeFunction(
4344 OMPRTL_NVPTX__kmpc_nvptx_teams_reduce_nowait_v2),
4345 Args);
4346 }
4347
4348 // 5. Build if (res == 1)
4349 llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".omp.reduction.done");
4350 llvm::BasicBlock *ThenBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".omp.reduction.then");
4351 llvm::Value *Cond = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpEQ(
4352 Res, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, /*V=*/1));
4353 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Cond, ThenBB, ExitBB);
4354
4355 // 6. Build then branch: where we have reduced values in the master
4356 // thread in each team.
4357 // __kmpc_end_reduce{_nowait}(<gtid>);
4358 // break;
4359 CGF.EmitBlock(ThenBB);
4360
4361 // Add emission of __kmpc_end_reduce{_nowait}(<gtid>);
4362 auto &&CodeGen = [Privates, LHSExprs, RHSExprs, ReductionOps,
4363 this](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &Action) {
4364 auto IPriv = Privates.begin();
4365 auto ILHS = LHSExprs.begin();
4366 auto IRHS = RHSExprs.begin();
4367 for (const Expr *E : ReductionOps) {
4368 emitSingleReductionCombiner(CGF, E, *IPriv, cast<DeclRefExpr>(*ILHS),
4369 cast<DeclRefExpr>(*IRHS));
4370 ++IPriv;
4371 ++ILHS;
4372 ++IRHS;
4373 }
4374 };
4375 llvm::Value *EndArgs[] = {ThreadId};
4376 RegionCodeGenTy RCG(CodeGen);
4377 NVPTXActionTy Action(
4378 nullptr, llvm::None,
4379 createNVPTXRuntimeFunction(OMPRTL_NVPTX__kmpc_end_reduce_nowait),
4380 EndArgs);
4381 RCG.setAction(Action);
4382 RCG(CGF);
4383 // There is no need to emit line number for unconditional branch.
4384 (void)ApplyDebugLocation::CreateEmpty(CGF);
4385 CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
4386}

4388const VarDecl *
4389CGOpenMPRuntimeNVPTX::translateParameter(const FieldDecl *FD,
4390 const VarDecl *NativeParam) const {
4391 if (!NativeParam->getType()->isReferenceType())
4392 return NativeParam;
4393 QualType ArgType = NativeParam->getType();
4394 QualifierCollector QC;
4395 const Type *NonQualTy = QC.strip(ArgType);
4396 QualType PointeeTy = cast<ReferenceType>(NonQualTy)->getPointeeType();
4397 if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<OMPCaptureKindAttr>()) {
4398 if (Attr->getCaptureKind() == OMPC_map) {
4399 PointeeTy = CGM.getContext().getAddrSpaceQualType(PointeeTy,
4400 LangAS::opencl_global);
4401 } else if (Attr->getCaptureKind() == OMPC_firstprivate &&
4402 PointeeTy.isConstant(CGM.getContext())) {
4403 PointeeTy = CGM.getContext().getAddrSpaceQualType(PointeeTy,
4404 LangAS::opencl_generic);
4405 }
4406 }
4407 ArgType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(PointeeTy);
4408 QC.addRestrict();
4409 enum { NVPTX_local_addr = 5 };
4410 QC.addAddressSpace(getLangASFromTargetAS(NVPTX_local_addr));
4411 ArgType = QC.apply(CGM.getContext(), ArgType);
4412 if (isa<ImplicitParamDecl>(NativeParam))
4413 return ImplicitParamDecl::Create(
4414 CGM.getContext(), /*DC=*/nullptr, NativeParam->getLocation(),
4415 NativeParam->getIdentifier(), ArgType, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
4416 return ParmVarDecl::Create(
4417 CGM.getContext(),
4418 const_cast<DeclContext *>(NativeParam->getDeclContext()),
4419 NativeParam->getBeginLoc(), NativeParam->getLocation(),
4420 NativeParam->getIdentifier(), ArgType,
4421 /*TInfo=*/nullptr, SC_None, /*DefArg=*/nullptr);
4422}

4424Address
4425CGOpenMPRuntimeNVPTX::getParameterAddress(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4426 const VarDecl *NativeParam,
4427 const VarDecl *TargetParam) const {
4428 assert(NativeParam != TargetParam &&
4429 NativeParam->getType()->isReferenceType() &&
4430 "Native arg must not be the same as target arg.");
4431 Address LocalAddr = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(TargetParam);
4432 QualType NativeParamType = NativeParam->getType();
4433 QualifierCollector QC;
4434 const Type *NonQualTy = QC.strip(NativeParamType);
4435 QualType NativePointeeTy = cast<ReferenceType>(NonQualTy)->getPointeeType();
4436 unsigned NativePointeeAddrSpace =
4437 CGF.CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(NativePointeeTy.getAddressSpace());
4438 QualType TargetTy = TargetParam->getType();
4439 llvm::Value *TargetAddr = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
4440 LocalAddr, /*Volatile=*/false, TargetTy, SourceLocation());
4441 // First cast to generic.
4442 TargetAddr = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
4443 TargetAddr, TargetAddr->getType()->getPointerElementType()->getPointerTo(
4444 /*AddrSpace=*/0));
4445 // Cast from generic to native address space.
4446 TargetAddr = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
4447 TargetAddr, TargetAddr->getType()->getPointerElementType()->getPointerTo(
4448 NativePointeeAddrSpace));
4449 Address NativeParamAddr = CGF.CreateMemTemp(NativeParamType);
4450 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(TargetAddr, NativeParamAddr, /*Volatile=*/false,
4451 NativeParamType);
4452 return NativeParamAddr;
4453}
4454
4455void CGOpenMPRuntimeNVPTX::emitOutlinedFunctionCall(
4456 CodeGenFunction &CGF, SourceLocation Loc, llvm::FunctionCallee OutlinedFn,
4457 ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> Args) const {
4458 SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 4> TargetArgs;
4459 TargetArgs.reserve(Args.size());
4460 auto *FnType = OutlinedFn.getFunctionType();
4461 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Args.size(); I < E; ++I) {
4462 if (FnType->isVarArg() && FnType->getNumParams() <= I) {
4463 TargetArgs.append(std::next(Args.begin(), I), Args.end());
4464 break;
4465 }
4466 llvm::Type *TargetType = FnType->getParamType(I);
4467 llvm::Value *NativeArg = Args[I];
4468 if (!TargetType->isPointerTy()) {
4469 TargetArgs.emplace_back(NativeArg);
4470 continue;
4471 }
4472 llvm::Value *TargetArg = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
4473 NativeArg,
4474 NativeArg->getType()->getPointerElementType()->getPointerTo());
4475 TargetArgs.emplace_back(
4476 CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(TargetArg, TargetType));
4477 }
4478 CGOpenMPRuntime::emitOutlinedFunctionCall(CGF, Loc, OutlinedFn, TargetArgs);
4479}
